 central questions from historical and systematic perspectives. In doing so, it helps define the framework of the discussion and advance recognition studies.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 4aIntersubjektivität. 4aPersonale Identität. 4aPersonsein. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Ethics & Moral Philosophy.2bisacsh  aPersonhood.  aintersubjectivity.  apersonal identity.1 aMooren, Nadine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Philosophy 2000 - 2014z9783110636949oZDB-23-GPH08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Complete Package 2014z9783110369526oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2014z9783110370393oZDB-23-DPH0 cEPUBz97831103919470 cprintz978311025412940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311025414340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110254143423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110254143/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2014  aZDB-23-DPHb2014  aZDB-23-GPHc2000d2014